The construction worker was flying home to Shandong, China, after losing his job in Singapore when he fell asleep and missed his connecting flight. 

'I had just enough to get a new ticket set to leave on Tuesday two days later, but I didn't have any more money for food,' he said.

'I didn't want to offend anyone but I needed power supply to cook the rice so I had to do it indoors.'

Eyewitnesses described the rice cooker as being 'hard to miss' with steam coming from it for over half an hour.

